## Update Protocol

### When to Check
- **STEP 4 (Self-Review)**: Check if your changes affect any maintained document
- **STEP 8 (PR)**: PR template includes a "Docs updated?" checkbox

### How to Update
1. Identify which documents are affected by your change
2. Update the document content
3. Include the doc update in the same PR as the code change
4. Note in the PR description which docs were updated

### What NOT to Do
- Don't create new documents without adding them to this registry
- Don't update docs in other repos — raise a Discussion to the Orchestrator
- Don't remove docs without updating this registry

---

## How to Customize

1. Add entries for each of your repositories
2. Fill in actual document paths and maintainers
3. Remove the `<!-- -->` comment blocks
4. Rename from `.template` to `.md`
